00:00:01.699 --> 00:00:06.180
Everyday you post pictures, updates and things
that are important to you, on Facebook. If

00:00:06.180 --> 00:00:09.910
you think about it, you’re basically writing
the story of your life as you go. Now how

00:00:09.910 --> 00:00:14.530
cool would it be if you could keep a copy
for yourself? Actually, you can. Just log

00:00:14.530 --> 00:00:18.500
into Facebook, click settings, and look for
the option to download a copy of your Facebook

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:22.980
data. This way you’ll have an interactive
copy of all your pictures, videos, messages

00:00:22.980 --> 00:00:26.090
and posts, saved right to your computer.

00:00:26.090 --> 00:00:29.920
Thinking outside the box a little can get
you some really amazing deals. For example,

00:00:29.920 --> 00:00:33.420
the next time you go buy something on eBay,
try searching for spelling mistakes on the

00:00:33.420 --> 00:00:37.230
items you’re looking for. Listings like these,
aren’t going to be found by very many people,

00:00:37.230 --> 00:00:41.540
so they’re less likely to get bid up in
price. So get in the habit of searching misspelled

00:00:41.540 --> 00:00:44.240
words, and see what kind of savings you can
score.

00:00:44.240 --> 00:00:48.790
There’s a fast and easy way to save online
receipts, pictures, and basically anything

00:00:48.790 --> 00:00:53.050
else that pops up on your computer screen.
It’s called screen capping and it’s unbelievably

00:00:53.050 --> 00:00:57.770
quick and easy to do. If you’re on a Mac,
hold shift, command, and the number 4, then

00:00:57.770 --> 00:01:01.489
select the area on the screen you want to
save. As soon as you let go, you’ll have

00:01:01.489 --> 00:01:05.819
an instant picture saved to your desktop.
Now if you’re using a PC, just press the

00:01:05.819 --> 00:01:09.340
“PrtScn” button to copy the screen to
the clipboard, then go ahead and paste the

00:01:09.340 --> 00:01:11.619
image into a program like windows paint.

00:01:11.619 --> 00:01:15.729
We’re halfway through the web tricks now,
so let’s take a quick break and tell Google

00:01:15.729 --> 00:01:19.799
to “do a barrel roll”. Surprisingly, you
